        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2995  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"DOCK10 is expressed in the hippocampus and localized in dendritic spines in hippocampal neurons\"\n- \"This showed that DOCK10 was present in the synaptosomal fraction, where it fractionated together with the postsynaptic density protein PSD-95 (Figure 4B), indicating a synaptic localization for DOCK10.\"\n- \"Figure 4D shows that DOCK10 was localized in the dendritic shaft and most strikingly in the dendritic spines in hippocampal neurons, which is compatible with a function of DOCK10 in dendritic spine morphogenesis. In addition, DOCK10 immunostaining in the spines localized adjacent to the presynaptic protein Bassoon (Figure 4E).\". Experimental description: - \"Male and female Pcp2-GFP or wild-type C57BL/6 mice (Jackson Laboratories, Bar Harbor, ME) and Swiss mice (Janvier Labs, St. Berthevin, France) used for organotypic cultures and for primary cultures of hippocampal neurons were housed at the animal house facility of the Institut de Génétique Moléculaire de Montpellier (Montpellier, France) or of the Integrati...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2995" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

